# Pre-Action Checklist

**Before taking ANY implementation action, STOP and run this checklist.**

## When This Applies

This checklist is MANDATORY before:
- Implementing features or components
- Modifying existing code
- Creating new files
- Executing implementation plans
- Making architectural changes
- Writing database queries or schema changes

## The Checklist

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PRE-ACTION CHECKLIST - Verify ALL before proceeding        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                             │
│  □ 1. CONFIDENCE: Do I have 95% confidence I understand?    │
│       → If NO: Ask clarifying questions first               │
│                                                             │
│  □ 2. BRAINSTORM: Is this creative/new work?                │
│       → If YES: Use brainstorming skill first               │
│                                                             │
│  □ 3. MCP-FIRST: Does this involve external data/APIs?      │
│       → Libraries/docs → Context7                           │
│       → Database/schema → Supabase MCP                      │
│       → Next.js runtime → next-devtools MCP                 │
│       → Styling/Tailwind → tailwindcss MCP                  │
│       → Linting errors → eslint MCP                         │
│       → UI testing → Playwright MCP                         │
│       → Production errors → Sentry MCP                      │
│       → PRs/issues → GitHub MCP                             │
│       → Charts/diagrams → AntVis Chart MCP                  │
│                                                             │
│  □ 4. COMPLEX REASONING: Does this involve...               │
│       → Choosing between 3+ approaches? → Sequential Think  │
│       → Debugging with multiple hypotheses? → Seq Think     │
│       → Ambiguous/conflicting requirements? → Seq Think     │
│       → Already failed once at this? → Seq Think            │
│                                                             │
│  □ 5. PLAN EXISTS: Is there an implementation plan?         │
│       → If NO for complex work: Create plan first           │
│       → If YES: Follow the plan steps                       │
│                                                             │
│  □ 6. SKILL MATCH: Does a skill apply to this work?         │
│       → Check skills table in AGENTS.md                     │
│       → Read and follow the matching skill                  │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## After Implementation

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  POST-ACTION CHECKLIST - Before claiming done               │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                             │
│  □ 1. VERIFY: Use verification-before-completion skill      │
│       → Run actual commands to confirm success              │
│       → Evidence before assertions                          │
│                                                             │
│  □ 2. DOCS: Update relevant documentation                   │
│       → docs/current-sprint.md                              │
│       → Implementation plans                                │
│       → Roadmap if scope changed                            │
│                                                             │
│  □ 3. LINT: Check for introduced errors                     │
│       → Run ReadLints on edited files                       │
│       → Fix any new errors                                  │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Quick Reference

| Trigger | Required Action |
|---------|-----------------|
| "implement X" | Full pre-action checklist |
| "create X" | Full pre-action checklist |
| "modify X" | Full pre-action checklist |
| "fix bug" | Systematic debugging skill first |
| "add feature" | Brainstorm + plan first |
| "continue" | Re-verify checklist, then proceed |

## Exceptions

Skip checklist ONLY for:
- Trivial edits (typos, comments, formatting)
- Reading/exploring code (no changes)
- Answering questions (no implementation)
- User explicitly says to skip

**When in doubt, run the checklist.**
